Reformed and Mennonites by careful scholarly discussion of the traditionally disputed questions.The papers gathered here were presented at the second phase of the international dialogue between the World Alliance of Reformed Churches (Presbyterian and Congregational) and the Mennonite World Conference. There are Reformed and Mennonite studies of the three topics, together with the responses of a philosopher of religion, a sociologist, a systematic theologian and a church historian. In the Introduction the dialogue is set in its historical and contemporary ecumenical context, and the Conclusion, drafted by the dialogue participants, has been forwarded to the two world bodies for their consideration and action. This important work will be relevant to all future scholarly research into the growing debate between Reformed and Mennonite communions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Mennonite.2bisacsh1 aBender, Ross T., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHiller, Harry H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoewen, Harry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoewen, Howard John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacRae, Andrew D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeynell, Hugo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Marlin E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNicol, Iain G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSell, Alan P. F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSinclair-Faulkner, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStackhouse, Max L., econtributor.4ctb4ht